The article is a transcript of remarks made by Vice President Mike Pence during a meeting at the Academia Diplomática Augusto Ramírez Ocampo in Bogotá, Colombia. Pence expressed support for the people of Venezuela, pledging assistance and stating that the United States will stand strong with President Juan Guaidó as the legitimate leader of Venezuela. He encouraged the attendees to have faith in the leaders for freedom in Venezuela and in the United States' commitment to their cause. The remarks were met with applause, and Pence concluded by introducing President Guaidó.